## GSD Workflow Variant

**This project uses: `build-gsd-cmux`**

Instead of `/build-gsd`, use `/build-gsd-cmux` for the BUILD stage.

**Why**: Cmux ad-hoc browser testing is easier for AI reasoning and provides visual confirmation in the terminal. The working selectors/timing are documented for the VERIFY stage to codify into Playwright tests.

---

## Cmux-Specific Configuration

### Services

| Service | Port | Start Command |
|---------|------|---------------|
| Server | 3000 | `npm run dev --workspace=packages/server` |
| Client | 5173 | `npm run dev --workspace=packages/client` |

### Test URL

```
http://localhost:5173
```

### Browser Surface Setup

```bash
# Start services in split panes
cmux new-split right
# Left pane: server
cmux send-surface --surface <left> "npm run dev --workspace=packages/server"
# Right pane: split for client
cmux send-surface --surface <right> "cmux new-split down"
cmux send-surface --surface <bottom-right> "npm run dev --workspace=packages/client"

# Wait for services (8 seconds)
sleep 8

# Open browser for testing
cmux browser open http://localhost:5173
```

