## VERIFY Stage: Cmux to Playwright

When running `/verify-gsd`, read Section 9 (Cmux Ad-Hoc Test Log) from the plan file to get:

1. **Working selectors** - Use these in Playwright page objects
2. **Timing observations** - Set appropriate timeouts
3. **Console errors** - Address any issues found during testing

### Example Translation

**Cmux ad-hoc**:
```bash
cmux browser surface:2 click "#btn-register"
cmux browser surface:2 fill "#auth-username" --text "testuser"
cmux browser surface:2 click "#submit-btn"
cmux browser surface:2 wait --text "Dashboard" --timeout-ms 5000
```

**Playwright test**:
```typescript
test("user can register", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/");
  await page.locator("#btn-register").click();
  await page.locator("#auth-username").fill("testuser");
  await page.locator("#submit-btn").click();
  await expect(page.locator(".dashboard-container")).toBeVisible({ timeout: 5000 });
});
```

