## API Contract

N/A - BoardBots uses WebSockets for real-time game state. No REST API contract verification needed.

---

## Architecture Notes

- Engine is pure logic with no I/O dependencies
- Client and Server both depend on Engine
- Server holds authoritative game state and broadcasts updates
- SQLite persists active game rooms
- WebSocket connection required for gameplay

---

## Monorepo Package Ownership

When spawning teammates for parallel work:

| Role | Owns | Avoids |
|------|------|--------|
| engine-dev | `packages/engine/**/*.ts` | client, server, e2e |
| client-dev | `packages/client/**/*.ts` | engine, server |
| server-dev | `packages/server/**/*.ts` | engine, client |
| e2e-tester | `packages/e2e/**/*.ts` | src files |
